trans-unit.source: Provides an interface that can extend a designer loader to support asynchronous loading of external components.
trans-unit.target: Gir et grensesnitt som kan utvide en designer laster for å støtte asynkron innlasting av eksterne komponenter.

trans-unit.source: A <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.DesignerLoader> can implement this interface to manage designer loading that involves external components.
trans-unit.target: En <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.DesignerLoader>kan implementerer dette grensesnittet for å administrere designer innlasting som involverer eksterne komponenter.</xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.DesignerLoader>

trans-unit.source: This interface also allows external components to initiate a reload of the design surface by calling <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.IDesignerLoaderService.Reload%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Dette grensesnittet kan også eksterne komponenter å starte en ny innlasting av utformingsoverflaten ved å kalle <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.IDesignerLoaderService.Reload%2A>.</xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.IDesignerLoaderService.Reload%2A>

trans-unit.source: A designer loader does not have to implement this interface if it does not require support for asynchronous loading.
trans-unit.target: En designer laster trenger ikke å implementerer dette grensesnittet hvis den ikke krever støtte for asynkron innlasting.

trans-unit.source: Designer loading using a custom implementation of the IDesignerLoaderService can occur in a variety of ways.
trans-unit.target: Spørringsutformer innlasting ved hjelp av en egendefinert implementering av IDesignerLoaderService kan oppstå på en rekke måter.

trans-unit.source: Sometimes external components are involved in the loading process.
trans-unit.target: Noen ganger eksterne komponenter er involvert i innlasting av prosessen.

trans-unit.source: To facilitate loading with external dependencies, the designer loader service interface provides a mechanism that determines when loading is complete and allows each portion of loading to signal that it has completed.
trans-unit.target: For å forenkle innlasting med eksterne avhengigheter har grensesnittet designer laster tjenesten en som bestemmer når innlasting er fullført, og gjør hver del for å laste Hvis du vil signalisere at den er fullført.

trans-unit.source: The IDesignerLoaderService typically determines when loading is complete by testing a counter that tracks the number of load dependencies remaining.
trans-unit.target: IDesignerLoaderService bestemmer vanligvis når nedlastingen er fullført ved å teste en teller som sporer antallet load avhengigheter gjenværende.

trans-unit.source: When each portion of the load completes, <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.IDesignerLoaderService.DependentLoadComplete%2A> is called, and the service decrements the counter.
trans-unit.target: Når hver del av belastningen er fullført, <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.IDesignerLoaderService.DependentLoadComplete%2A>kalles, og tjenesten reduseres telleren.</xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.IDesignerLoaderService.DependentLoadComplete%2A>

trans-unit.source: To set the number of dependent load processes, call <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.IDesignerLoaderService.AddLoadDependency%2A> once for each load process that calls <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.IDesignerLoaderService.DependentLoadComplete%2A> when its loading is complete.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du vil angi antallet avhengige load prosesser, kan du kalle <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.IDesignerLoaderService.AddLoadDependency%2A>én gang for hver load prosess som kaller <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.IDesignerLoaderService.DependentLoadComplete%2A>Når nedlastingen er fullført.</xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.IDesignerLoaderService.DependentLoadComplete%2A> </xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.IDesignerLoaderService.AddLoadDependency%2A>

trans-unit.source: When the final loading is complete, the service calls <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.IDesignerLoaderHost.EndLoad%2A> on the loader host.
trans-unit.target: Når endelig innlasting er fullført, service-kall <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.IDesignerLoaderHost.EndLoad%2A>på verten laster.</xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.IDesignerLoaderHost.EndLoad%2A>

trans-unit.source: Registers an external component as part of the load process managed by this interface.
trans-unit.target: Registrerer en ekstern komponent som en del av belastning prosessen administreres av dette grensesnittet.

trans-unit.source: Call AddLoadDependency once for each external object participating in the load process.
trans-unit.target: Kall AddLoadDependency én gang for hver eksternt objekt deltar i load prosessen.

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.IDesignerLoaderService.DependentLoadComplete%2A> is called when the work of the load process is done.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.IDesignerLoaderService.DependentLoadComplete%2A>kalles når arbeidet fra innlastingsprosessen er fullført.</xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.IDesignerLoaderService.DependentLoadComplete%2A>

trans-unit.source: Signals that a dependent load has finished.
trans-unit.target: Signaliserer som en avhengige belastning er fullført.

trans-unit.source: This method is called to signal that a dependent loading operation has completed.
trans-unit.target: Denne metoden kalles for å signalisere at avhengige innlasting-operasjonen er fullført.

trans-unit.source: Call DependentLoadComplete once for every process that was registered by calling <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.IDesignerLoaderService.AddLoadDependency%2A>, which has already completed.
trans-unit.target: Kall DependentLoadComplete én gang for alle prosesser som ble registrert ved å kalle <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.IDesignerLoaderService.AddLoadDependency%2A>, som allerede er fullført.</xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.Serialization.IDesignerLoaderService.AddLoadDependency%2A>

trans-unit.source: If the dependent load succeeds, the caller sets the `successful` parameter to `true` and passes either an empty collection or `null` to the `errorCollection` parameter.
trans-unit.target: Hvis den avhengige lastingen lykkes oppkaller angir den `successful` parameter `true` , og sender en tom samling eller `null` til den `errorCollection` parameteren.

trans-unit.source: If the dependent load encounters errors, the caller sets the `successful` parameter to `false` and passes a collection of exceptions that indicate the reason or reasons for failure to the `errorCollection` parameter.
trans-unit.target: Hvis den avhengige lastingen oppstår feil, oppkalleren angir den `successful` parameter `false` , og sender en samling av unntak som angir årsaken eller årsaker til at du kan ikke den `errorCollection` parameteren.

trans-unit.source: <xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref> if the load of the designer is successful; <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref> if errors prevented the load from finishing.
trans-unit.target: <xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref>Hvis innlasting av designer er fullført. <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""> </xref> Hvis feil forhindret innlasting fra ferdig.

trans-unit.source: A collection of errors that occurred during the load, if any.
trans-unit.target: En samling av feil som oppstod under belastningen, hvis noen.

trans-unit.source: If no errors occurred, pass either an empty collection or <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""></xref>.
trans-unit.target: Hvis ingen feil oppstod, sendes en tom samling eller <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: Reloads the design document.
trans-unit.target: Laster inn på nytt design-dokument.

trans-unit.source: Any object can call this method to request that the loader reload the design document.
trans-unit.target: Et objekt kan kalle denne metoden for å be om som laster inn design-dokument.

trans-unit.source: If the loader supports reloading and complies with the reload, the designer loader can return `true`.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du laster støtter laste og samsvarer med inn, designer-laster kan returnere `true`.

trans-unit.source: Otherwise, it returns `false`, indicating that the reload will not occur.
trans-unit.target: Ellers returneres `false`, som angir at inn ikke gjennomføres.

trans-unit.source: Callers cannot rely on the reload happening immediately; the designer loader can schedule this for some other time, or it can try to reload at once.
trans-unit.target: Brukere kan ikke avhenger av Last skjer umiddelbart. designer-laster kan planlegge dette en stund, eller den kan prøve å laste inn samtidig.

trans-unit.source: The caller can display a message to the user if the designer cannot be reloaded.
trans-unit.target: Oppkalleren kan vises en melding til brukeren når designer ikke kan lastes inn på nytt.

trans-unit.source: <xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref> if the reload request is accepted, or <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref> if the loader does not allow the reload.
trans-unit.target: <xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref>Hvis inn forespørselen godtas, eller <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""> </xref> Hvis lasteren ikke tillater at det Last inn på nytt.
